<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-124] MethodInvocation is missing a getThis() (or equivalent) method</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-124</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current (r896125) revision of MethodInvocation does not expose a method for accessing the object on which the method is being invoked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the AOP world, I think this is the JoinPoint.getThis() method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In any case, such a method is necessary to test permissions at the instance level (e.g.: &quot;lightsaber:wield:blue&quot;, where &quot;blue&quot; is obtained from the instance on which the &quot;wield()&quot; method of the &quot;Lightsaber&quot; class is called.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
